## 2. Register the domain — DONE: truewise.dev (2026-07-13)

Chose `.dev` over `.us` to avoid the `.us` nexus attestation. `.dev` has no residency
requirement and is on the HSTS preload list, so browsers force HTTPS automatically. ~$12–15/yr.

## 3. Connect Cloudflare Pages (auto-deploy) — TODO

- Cloudflare dashboard → Pages → Create a project → Connect to the GitHub `truewise` repo.
- Build settings: **Framework preset = None**, **Build command = (leave empty)**,
  **Build output directory = `site`**. The site is static, so there is no build step yet.
- Set the production branch to `main`. Every merge to `main` then auto-deploys `site/`.
- Add the custom domain **`truewise.dev`** in the Pages project. If the domain is registered
  at Cloudflare, DNS + HTTPS are automatic. If it is registered elsewhere, either move the
  nameservers to Cloudflare or add the CNAME that the Pages "custom domain" screen shows you.

The `deploy` job in `.github/workflows/ci.yml` is a placeholder note — Cloudflare Pages
deploys directly from the repo, so no deploy token is needed unless you later prefer to push
from Actions.

